caption: Cozy place with friendly workers, food is really good too. Cery have they have dine-in. Definitely will come back for more

(Translated by Google) It is small, but very good, very tasty, they serve a delicious lamb, they speak Spanish too. They are excellent and fast with service, their food is fantastic. Be sure to try the chees cake, it is special!  (Original) Es pequeño, pero muy bueno, muy sabroso, sirven un cordero esquisito, hablan español también. Son excelentes y rápidos con el servicio, su comida es fantástica. No dejes de probar el chees cake, es especial!
Money waisted on overpriced disgusting food and drinks :(
One of the best brunch places in the neighborhood. I have brought my dog to eat with friends there a few times and we both always have a great meal.
Good food and service. Love the Someone pinch me!

I have been a few times and let me first tell you, just go here for brunch. The lunch and dinner is good but far to expensive for what it is. The brunch is also kind of expensive but not as bad as lunch and dinner.
Delicious food, tasty cocktails and great service! The lobster roll is fantastic and the lobster and smoky eggplant pasta is incredible. Never had a bad meal here.

The restaurant is super amazing. The service was quick, friendly and professional. The food was amazing, we had the soup, fries and salad - all 3 dishes were perfect, you can really test the love and passion the chef has. Super recommend!!!!!! The only reason I chose to give the restaurant 4 stars and not 5 is the pricing of the food. I thought it was a little bit too expensive. But still I'd go back, it was really good.
Nice lunch but I heard brunch is much better (Saturday and Sunday) only!
Fantastic brunch and friendly staff! I go very often with friends and we all alway have a good meal.
Awesome place. The menu is stellar and the staff is lovely. Victor the bar manager is extremely cool, and is passionate about their recipes. Definitely recommended!!
Excellent food and service, however it's  extremely pricey!
Decent burger, but the bun to beef ratio was way off. I think I discarded like 25% of the bread by the time I was done. The fries are really good too.

Yesterday was our first time we went to this good restaurant. But It is definitely not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the excellent service, with the magnificent  cuisine and wine and with the honest charge. We will no doubt return there in a short time.
The kale and baked eggs brunch is the best !
Liked the oysters and truffle potatoes! Oh, did I mention their great cocktails? Great neighborhood spot.

This is a take-away order review. Food only. Ordered the burger with fries. Meat and bred were good, tasty. Raw meat taste. Fries socked with oil. Uneatable. A shame. Otherwise it could have been a 3-star.

One of the most annoying and over priced restaurants I had visited lately. We went there for a dinner. All main dishes cost at least 30$. They didn't serve half of the menu. The dishes were served poorly. Too pretentious in my opinion. Probably if the dishes were priced fairly I wouldn't write this review but for a 30-40$ dish I expect much more.

Very nice and cozy place, due to covid19 tables set outside on the closed for the traffic block in very quiet neighborhood.  The food and service was very good. We even had live saxophone what made dinner very romantic.  This place required advanced booking and they take hold of your credit card with a charge of $25 per person in case if you not would show up. However they were very flexible,  I came 30 minutes late (I called them and warned of me getting late) and we have no problem.
One of my favorites for delivery or at the new patio area. Order the burger. It's magnificent. Also the cocktails really bring it. Great place for a date or even hanging with friends.
Food ad service is great! They are much better for dinner and a little over priced.
Everything was superb. Best lobster roll I've had in the city. So often places in Williamsburg disappoint but this is a nice change!

Blown away by the grilled chicken and the grilled kale. Both were exceptional, much better than the average New American restaurant. The clam linguine was good, but not as surprising. Good social distancing measures on the front patio.
I regularly arrive grabbing some food in here. I like the quick customer service and well made dishes. Keep it up.

I used to love this place and didn't mind spending extra for quality but now the menu is so small that there isn't enough options to please everyone. Bummer. Update - no more delivery unless it's GrubHub. Lame. B-bye Update - now they take phone orders and give a discount. Update - now they won't take cash. This place is run by crazy people!

Been treating myself to take out from this place and it’s always amazing. The burger is great and we also had the mussels and fries. I’m in a better mood after eating their amazing food. Definitely order direct if you can, it helps them out and they even will give you a discount on alcohol if you do.
Fantastic and fresh food, I loved the ambience this place has, and the workers were very welcoming. Will definitely visit here when I’m around.

I often take my friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The the cooking is fantastic and the team is very friendly and cooperative. Every time  we eat in this place we pass a pleasant evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.
Server forgot to put in our order for v-day dinner. After waiting an hour plus we were brought out raw chicken and a rare steak (ordered well). What a joke .
Great spot, impressive food!

This place has to be one of the best-kept secrets in the area! There's no need to compromise: the food at CH is decadent and healthy all at once. Plates don't just look beautiful; the food is always perfectly seasoned. My personal favorites: grilled kale, little gem salad, fingerling potatoes, tabbouleh, prawn tagliatelle, NY strip steak, pork chop, tarte citron, and the Basque cheesecake! Plus a fantastic wine list. You'd spend WAY more for the same high quality ingredients elsewhere...this is an amazing spot for locals and it's definitely worth the trip if you're not from the neighborhood!
one of the best steak I ever had, all the food was fresh and delicious, go for the eggplant soup as well
Warm vibes good food. Love the apple jam. And their croissants are perfect.

Some of the best food & wine pairings in Brooklyn! And the staff is both attentive and friendly. What more could you ask for? Shout outs to Gina and rest of the crew for making each dining experience special.

My boyfriend and I just moved to the neighborhood a few months ago and this quickly became our absolute favorite spot around. The food is always amazing and they do a great job of switching up specials and trying out new and creative dishes. The space is cozy and casual and definitely allows for customers to feel relaxed. The best part though is the staff! Always accommodating and friendly. Gina, Christina, and the rest are the best!
This is a really nice place

Great cozy place Food is very tasty . We had octopus salad, lobster with avocado and a steak . All highly recommended. For desert we had a very tasty cheese cake. Prices are reasonable and quality is high. We will definitely come back!
We had a great dinner !!!! Seems to be a very talented chef- great value for money . I will come again for sure!
Fresh and lovely! Delicious American dishes with impeccable service. The roasted vegetables are perfection. Highly recommend this restaurant and can’t wait to go back.
Great atmosphere. Amazing food. Highly recommend the wild caught fish
(Translated by Google) Very well  Well done! Excellent Quality  (Original) Muy  bien  Muy bien excelente Calidad
I would highly recommend this place! Excellent spot and friendly vibes, the food was incredible, so flavorful and innovative.
This was one of my favorite places ever. Came here at least weekly. The new chef came in and doesn’t get the place or the regulars. Concord, this isn’t you. Do better than him.

Embarrassingly terrible service. Apparently they “don’t offer additional sides” what? We spent $250 on dinner there and we were not allowed to order an additional order of fries for our guest. This was something we wanted to pay for but instead we got “sorry, we don’t do additional sides!” Well, sorry, we won’t be coming back.
Cute place.  Cute NY Brooklyn town - Williamsburg...  L line... Graham stop.  Great service!  Outdoor seating.  Small portions.  Limited menu.  Pricey.

Ridiculously small and claustrophobic. Miss Gina Buck who is the so-called hiring manager here is a joke. No respect for candidates or their time. Too much of a coward to follow up and let people know exactly how they were reviewed. Would rather have them waste their time, money on transportation and overall effort to be ghosted on in hopes of a response. Gina. I hope you read this and get it together. You are extremely unprofessional.

A great little place! We ordered a bunch of vegetable plates to share and the portions were twice as big as I expected for the price and for it being a nice place. The wait staff were all lovely and accommodating. I would recommend this for any diet.

Brunch used to be good here. Have been going here for 3 years. Now there is a new chef, far less options for brunch, higher prices, and food is just bland. I paid $20 for runny eggs with no seasoning, breakfast potatoes with no seasoning, and dry biscuits.
Great food and atmosphere. My girlfriend and I eat here a few times a month and have always had great experiences.
Quality food, but nothing mind-blowing. My roast chicken was good, but for $35 for a half-a chicken, it should be incredible. Additionally, it took 55 minutes for our meal to come out.
Food isn’t that great
Nice and cozy place, great ambient and perfectly prepared food with nice presentation. Great place to go with your couple or friend to have nice brunch or lunch
Great mimosas. okay breakfast burritos. Chill atmosphere.

Concord Hill has been one of my go-to's since moving to Williamsburg. It's a warm, welcoming, and tasty choice all around. Servers are good, kitchen is up to date and fresh, and I've never had a bad meal there for lunch, brunch or dinner. This place gets busy so I recommend reservations but such a great place!

One of my go-to neighborhood joints. Simple food with fresh ingredients. The warm vegetable bowl is a nice change of pace from the traditional brunch fare you find in most restaurants. So is the loco moco bowl.

Come here fairly often with my girlfriend and the food is always pretty good. Nothing to write home about, but tasty and have some nice healthy options. Came the other night and prices have gone up quite a bit it seems. The quality and consistency isn’t really at the level of the new pricing.  This was an easy and laidback spot to get out of the apt and have a solid meal, but probably won’t be back nearly as often.

Ate here for my sister's bachelorette party,  it was wonderful! We had a reservation for 8 people, the restaurant is quite cozy and the food is fantastic. Lots of vegetable inspired dishes--highly recommend the sweet potato fries, bacon croquettes and the veggie burger. The dessert cakes were amazing too. Would dine here again!
Beautiful and delicious under soft lighting, good music and kind people. Sweet potato fries....

What a lovely spot.  Everything we ordered was absolutely delicious.  We started with the bacon croquettes and a salmon carpacio on special.  Chicken sandwich as the main was so crispy and tangy with a side of fries that were what you wish McDonald's tasted like.  The food is comfort without being too simple. The friendly staff is a perfect compliment to the cozy ambiance.  The wine, elevated, affordable and we'll paired to the dishes.  We will be back!

Really cute place to go for dinner. Lots of veggie dishes and comfort food. We got the special croquettes and they were really tasty. Also love the kale salad and Brussels sprouts and sweet potato fries. Nice selection of wine as well.

Jeez man, I never leave reviews, but I came away from here feeling very frustrated with my experience. Listen, it's not hard to get a steak frites right, and when it's not right and you see the customer is disappointed and hasn't touched it, then at least apologize and make an effort to compensate them in some small way. And vermouth is served in ice with a slice of orange, btw. Merci!
Consistently delicious, amazing service. One of my favorite places in New York!
Very average. Average burger. Pretty inattentive service. So cramped that difficult to tune out of the conversations next to you. Won't be back in a rush.
Delicious food and great service

Honestly the best little restaurant ever! Super great friendly service, the foods looks so easy but has tons of complexity to it. Great place for date night, friends dinner, chill night. It’s a locals go-to spot.

Cozy restaurant. Not for groups, but there is bar seating. Food was good, drinks were good and staff were nice. Prices are as expected and the menu was pretty expansive with good options. Recommended.
Delicious drinks!! Oysters were fresh and delicious
Small, but nice place
Excellent food and service. A hidden gem in the neighborhood.
Great place, great food and service, if you get there between 4pm and 7pm you will get happy hour $1 oyster, burger and beer for $10, I will definitely come back
My favorite dish is the linguini pasta with the shrimp
Go to for any meal
Mom ate here!
Great food and cozy atmosphere. Delicious vegetable focused menu :) #vegetarianfriendly #cozy #datenight #localspot
Great food and staff
One of my favorite burgers. It's done in a no glitz kind of way that is simple but yummy.

Small cozy brunch spot. Didn't get a chance to try any cocktails but the cold brew was good and i may have been more tempted by the Other Half on tap. Food was very tasty, hard to pick because everything sounded good.
Good casual spot in the neighborhood for a light meal.

Went there to have a salad, of all things, and Cobb was great! The brussel sprouts were also very crispy, just how I like em (maybe just a lil over🤷🏻‍♂️), and went well with an excellent sour wheat ale I saw for the first time! Good staff and service too!
Really enjoyable brunch with all of the classics done well. They also have a front seating area for when it's nice outside.
Amazing food and service! The veggie burger was so delicious and fresh.
Love this place. – Some call it my office.
Love the atmosphere here, and I order from here all the time. Great food.
Love it here. Great food. Awesome service. Local vibes.
Quaint cozy place, excellent service. Food was good, but nothing to write home about and a bit overpriced for what it is (rating based on dinner).
Six of us met here to remember a friend who had recently passed on.  Everyone was blown away by the food and the service. Its a light airy little place and a good value.
Food was fantastic, service great!
Great brunch spot. Love sharing a few plates with a friend here.

Friends and I had planned for dinner at another spot but it was closed for kitchen maintenance, so we popped into Concord Hill..and we didn't want to leave. We shared the cheeseburger (my new favorite),  the warm salad, a pasta dish and a dinner special and everything was FLAWLESS. So delicious..my mouth is watering thinking about it. Such a great little place!
Such a solid, simple menu. Best for small groups (2-3), as it’s quite small.
Amazing brunch. Try the fried chicken Sandwich!
One of my favorite restaurants off Graham avenue. Food is great, everyone is friendly and very accommodating. One of the few places where sitting at the bar is more fun. A++++
cozy, comfortable and delicious! great drink menu too!
Never had a disappointing, much less lackluster, meal here. Simple but tasty potent meals
The breakfast burrito was delicious. I also got their house-made limeade (asked for no simple syrup). It was intensely tart and magically amazing! I also love the music they play here.
Phenomenal food and drinks and friendly staff. So happy we found this place!

Love this place! Cute little American bistro. Friendly staff. Delicious brunch. Spicy bloody Mary's. They will have a great $10 Burger&Beer special from time to time. Cozy inside. Sun-drenched front patio seating when it's warm out, and a great place to hipster-watch.:)
Lots of food, but dish wasn't the best I ever had.

I was really excited about this restaurant but our brunch was super disappointing. The food wasn't great, and I got food poisoning the next day, I think from the burger. The only redeeming thing was the loaded tater tots, which were very good.
Great food. Try the veggie burger
Came in on Labor Day Weekend (luckily, not as crowded as usual) and ordered the burger special. Got a massive burger and fries, all for $16. High quality food for a solid price.

(Translated by Google) This restaurant is very good and has a different menu, where the American cuisine is presented in different options. I recommend.  (Original) Este restaurante é muito bom e tem um cardápio diferente, onde a gastronomia americana é apresentada em diferentes opções. Recomendo.
It was ok

Good food. I am someone who likes to know that the meat coming from the kitchen isn't packed with hormones and antibiotics. This place could neither confirm or deny this, which means the meat they use isn't worth eating. Still solid
Amazing food, a hidden gem!
Breakfast burrito hit the spot
Minimal wait, great food, more than reasonable prices. Definitely going back
Great brunch.
The food was amazing. We had it delivered last Friday and, not only did it get there fast, but the delivery guy was the bomb! Friendly and polite! 👍😁
Nice and comfy
Favorite Neighborhood Eats.

I had a 9 o'clock reservation and got there 30 mins in advance and they sat me down right away. The reception was friendly and they seated us right away. The 1st waitress (did not get her name) was really nice. She did not see us initially,  bit as she glanced over, she kicked ot into gear and grabbed a fresh bottle of water. She then suggested the corn...wow, I love corn and it was grilled to perfection.  Slightly crunchy on outside and juicy on the inside. Afterwards, Krinstina took over and it was a real joy. She had a great sense of humor, and gave us a rundown of what she liked. We went with the Kale Caesar, Crispy Brussels Sprouts and the Chicken which they made into a special. Now, this night they ran out of steak and pork chops, which to me shows the quick turnover they get. The restaurant was full including the bar. Between the service of Kristina and the others, along with the owner; kept us entertained. Had the ice cream with expresso shot that ended the meal or the dining experience.  Also had a wine from Italy, called Skerjl?  It was crisp with strong hints of orange. If I could stay linger I would. Quaint place, simple decorations. Who cares about decor when food and service is great!  A definite gem in the neighborhood!
Consistently delicious.
Nice atmosphere. We go here often because its so close, but it does dissapoint sometimes.
Food is off the hook. Great eats, great service...and the delivery guy was the bomb! This place rocks!

Depending on what you're looking for, Concord Hill could be great. It was a cute space, good service. Also, the drinks were great (my Kir Royale was delish!). However, the food menu was very limited. Not sure if it was the time of day we went (4pm) but we we're hoping for a full menu, which they didn't have at that particular time. We ended up with French fries, which were tasty.
Comfortable space...  Great service
Big warm salad! It's great! Also, very sweet decor.
Amazing food! Try the pan roasted chicken and the big warm salad with steak. Crispy Brussels are a MUST!

This is the best place on Graham Avenue! Way better than Mesa Coyoacan next door. Happy hour every day from 4 to 6 PM has amazing deals including one $1 oysters and a double cheeseburger tallboy combination for $10. And the burger is damn good.
We ordered a lot of different things off the menu and all was truly excellent. Music was great also light jams and 70s rock

A tasty and chill small, local restaurant. I've visited twice now. Once for happy hour when you can eat $1 oysters and drink half priced wine, and once for brunch on a Sunday. On both occasions the full menu was available (which is a good thing because I tend to want to order what they've ran out of) and both the food and the service were outstanding. Sitting outside at their sidewalk tables gives you a great opportunity to do people watching in one of the most interesting Brooklyn neighborhoods. Will keep coming back .

I came here for brunch on a Saturday afternoon.  I ordered the fried chicken sandwich since it sounded tasty.  The sandwich was delicious.  The chicken was juicy and crispy.  The spicy slaw and sriracha mayo gave it a little kick.  I can say that the fried chicken sandwich here was better than shake shack's and fuku's versions.  It also came with a lot of fries and they were very crispy.  The prices were surprisingly decent for brunch in the neighborhood.  I would return to try their other dishes.

Table of four last night and everyone was really happy with their meals!  Every main and appetizer we got was delicious - Yucca, beets/burrata, oysters, adobo pork belly, sasso chicken, salmon, and a sea bass special (mine) which was in a divine broth with two potato croquettes.  Definitely delicious
Delicious , fresh, not too heavy.  Good find for brunch
Love the salads, and the lemonade. This is one of our local go to's

My experience here was a bit of a conundrum. We waited about 15 min for a table for 2. Reasonable for a Saturday night. Ordered quickly- oddly our server "downsold" us on the wine- from a $40 bottle we were interested in to the $18/500ml house wine. It turned out to be pretty good so maybe she was just being honest? They were out of the lamb shoulder, which we wanted to try but it was 9pm and it was busy so I guess that's understandable. Had the toasts, skirt steak and chicken sandwich. The toasts and steak were great. They chicken sandwich a bit weird- the chicken version of a french dip; didn't quite work. Hopefully this place improves. Could be good.
